Source: shadowfetch-meta
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Shadowfetch Project <maintainers@shadowfetch.example>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://shadowfetch.example/

Package: shadowfetch-desktop
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 shadowfetch-themes (= ${binary:Version}),
 shadowfetch-defaults (= ${binary:Version}),
 shadowfetch-branding (= ${binary:Version}),
 shadowfetch-welcome (= ${binary:Version}),
 shadowfetch-creative-base (= ${binary:Version}),
 kde-plasma-desktop,
 sddm,
 pipewire,
 pipewire-pulse,
 wireplumber,
 network-manager,
 flatpak,
 plasma-discover-backend-flatpak
Description: Shadowfetch creative workstation (KDE Plasma edition)
 Shadowfetch is a Debian-based Linux distribution for visual artists,
 musicians, and video creators. This meta-package installs the full
 Shadowfetch desktop experience, including the KDE Plasma session,
 the creative-app baseline, themes, branding, and the welcome tool.

Package: shadowfetch-creative-base
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 gimp, krita, inkscape, blender,
 darktable, rawtherapee,
 ardour, audacity, lmms, carla,
 lsp-plugins, x42-plugins, calf-plugins,
 kdenlive, obs-studio,
 ffmpeg,
 fonts-inter, fonts-jetbrains-mono
Description: Shadowfetch creative app baseline
 Installs the core set of creative applications Shadowfetch users
 expect: 2D, 3D, photo, audio, and video tools.

Package: shadowfetch-nvidia
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 nvidia-driver,
 nvidia-settings,
 nvidia-vaapi-driver,
 libnvidia-encode1,
 firmware-nvidia-gsp
Recommends:
 nvidia-cuda-toolkit,
 nvidia-prime
Description: Shadowfetch NVIDIA driver bundle
 Pulls in the proprietary NVIDIA stack used by Shadowfetch by default.
 A first-boot hook removes this stack if no NVIDIA GPU is detected, so
 it is safe to install on non-NVIDIA hardware.
